 :PC-ism: /P-C-izm/ n. A piece of code or coding technique that takes
advantage of the unprotected single-tasking environment in IBM PCs and the
like running DOS, e.g., by busy-waiting on a hardware register, direct
diddling of screen memory, or using hard timing loops. Compare {ill-behaved},
{vaxism}, {unixism}. Also, `PC-ware' n., a program full of PC-isms on a
machine with a more capable operating system. Pejorative.